FBIS3-57614 "drsov019_a_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-019 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Jan 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Deputy Minister Gromov's `Puzzling' Presence in China PM2701200594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 28 Jan 94 First Edition p 4 PM2701200594 Moscow IZVESTIYA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Vladimir Skosyrev and Konstantin Eggert report: "General Gromov in Minister Kozyrev's Suite"] [Excerpts] Russia's Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin may possibly visit the PRC soon. This was announced at the conclusion of talks between Russia's Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev and his Chinese counterpart Qian Qichen. [passage omitted] The presence of Deputy Defense Minister Boris Gromov as member of the Russian delegation is somewhat puzzling. He took no part in the talks between the foreign ministers and, in his own words, had arrived "to take a look at China."
